cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.SY

This paper deals with the inference of network structure and dynamics, which is a core topic in computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new framework for analyzing and designing algorithms, which involves the use of distance-based inference algorithms. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance and optimality of the algorithms, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
